MAC Settings:

1) Open the terminal
2) Type the command: nano ~/.zshrc or vim ~/.zshrc
3) For Vim ~/.zshrchit on the 'i' button
4) Then start typing the PAth. e.g. export JAVA_HOME=/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/jdk-21.jdk/Contents/Home
5) and set the end point e.g.       export PATH=$JAVA_HOME/bin:$PATH
6) Hit on the 'esc' button
7) Type :wq
8) It will redirect to the terminal
9) To save changes successfully type the command: source ~/.zshrc
10) Verify the environment variable: java --version
11) To get the path of the variable type this command: echo $PATH 
    e.g. echo $JAVA_HOME: /Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/jdk-21.jdk/Contents/Home
